COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
CMD ["uvicorn", "app.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8080"]
```

âœ… **MUST CREATE:**
```
# .dockerignore
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
.git/
uploads/
test_videos/
```

âœ… **MUST CREATE:**
```yaml
# cloudbuild.yaml (if using Cloud Build)
steps:
  - name: 'gcr.io/cloud-builders/docker'
    args: ['build', '-t', 'gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/biome-agent', '.']
  - name: 'gcr.io/cloud-builders/docker'
    args: ['push', 'gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/biome-agent']
  - name: 'gcr.io/google.com/cloudsdktool/cloud-sdk'
    args:
      - 'gcloud'
      - 'run'
      - 'deploy'
      - 'biome-agent'
      - '--image=gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/biome-agent'
      - '--region=us-central1'
      - '--memory=4Gi'
      - '--timeout=300s'
```

âŒ **DON'T CREATE:** docs/deployment-guide.md (waste of time)

